cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.CR 

The paper deals with deep neural networks (DNNs) and their use in safety-critical systems, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The focus on DNNs and their accuracy on test sets suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), while the use of DNNs in image analysis suggests cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also proposes an approach for identifying root causes of DNN errors, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SE (Software Engineering). Finally, the paper addresses safety concerns, which could place it in cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
